						               													<description>Educational board game 'Ekosystem&amp;quot; is designed for high school students of grade VIII which are familiar with ecology. Purpose of this game is to help students revise information about ecology.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game box includes: 12 tiles with questions and tasks, chart with correct answers, 4 pawns and a dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Game is played by 4 players. They randomly choose pawns' colours and thus are assigned names: green &amp;ndash; producer, blue &amp;ndash; primary consumer(herbivore), red &amp;ndash; secondary consumer(carnivore), black &amp;ndash; decomposer(saprotroph). Green pawn moves first, next is blue, then red, and black last. Players move their pawns on the board by the number of fields indicated by the dice.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The are 12 marked fields on the board. Whenever a player's pawn steps on any of those fields he takes a questions and tasks tile with the number of field he stepped onto. He has to read a question or task aloud an immediately answer it. Illustrations near the board's edge might help. Answer is then checked with the chart.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The winner is the player who acquires the most points. For every correct answer player is awarded 3 points. Bonus for track completion: 1st place &amp;ndash; 3 points, 2nd place &amp;ndash; 2 points, 3rd place &amp;ndash; 1 point. For incorrect answers players have to skip a turn. If there are any unanswered questions behind the last pawn, players that have reached finish line can try to answer them.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
